<Base
  title="About — Ken Ahrens"
  description="Ken Ahrens — co-founder and CEO of Speedscale, long-time open source tinkerer."
>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <img class="about-photo" src="/img/profile.jpg" alt="Ken Ahrens" />

  <p>
    I'm a proud family patriarch and occasional developer of ill repute. At work
    I'm co-founder and CEO at Speedscale, where we help companies test
    applications so they run faster with fewer errors in production.
  </p>

  <p>
    Outside of work I've been an open source person for a long time. My dad got
    me onto Ubuntu in 2007 (he was putting Linux on the lowest-powered box in the
    house to use as a firewall), and I've run Linux at home ever since. These
    days that's a k3s homelab on a Raspberry Pi and a growing pile of AI models
    running locally on hardware I already own. I worked at Pentaho back in 2014
    when everything was open source, and that mindset stuck.
  </p>

  <h2>Experience</h2>

